What this implies for minds and models

If we extend the metaphor:

A mind can be thought of as something that builds a model of the world by combining many “views.”

Those views might come from:
	•	different senses
	•	different memories
	•	different experiences
	•	different people

The clearer the model, the more independent perspectives you can integrate.

This is essentially how science works:

Many measurements → reconcile differences → converge on a model.

