Memory as reconstruction

For humans, memory isn’t a perfect recording.
Psychology shows it’s more like reconstruction each time you recall something.

Each recall is influenced by:
	•	current context
	•	new information
	•	interpretation

So even human memory is partly recomputed each time.

In that sense, both human and AI cognition rely heavily on rebuilding models from available signals, not replaying exact recordings.

